# Typhon: UowRegistryEntry State Machine
# Shows legal states and transitions for UoW Registry entries

direction: down

title: |md
  # UoW Registry Entry Lifecycle
  State transitions for `UowRegistryEntry` — normal path and crash recovery
|

# ── States ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

free: "Free\n(slot available)" {
  shape: circle
  style.fill: "#c8e6c9"
  style.stroke: "#388e3c"
  style.bold: true
}

pending: "Pending\n(UoW active)" {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#fff3e0"
  style.stroke: "#f57c00"
  style.font-color: "#e65100"
  style.bold: true
}

wal_durable: "WalDurable\n(WAL FUA complete)" {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#bbdefb"
  style.stroke: "#1976d2"
  style.bold: true
}

committed: "Committed\n(data pages checkpointed)" {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#1565c0"
  style.font-color: white
  style.stroke: "#0d47a1"
  style.bold: true
}

void: "Void\n(crash recovery)" {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#ffcdd2"
  style.stroke: "#c62828"
  style.font-color: "#b71c1c"
  style.bold: true
}

# ── Normal Path ───────────────────────────────────────────────

free -> pending: "AllocateUowId()\n[WAL record + group commit]" {
  style.stroke: "#388e3c"
  style.bold: true
}

pending -> wal_durable: "WAL flush\n(FUA complete)" {
  style.stroke: "#1976d2"
}

wal_durable -> committed: "Checkpoint\n(pages fsync'd)" {
  style.stroke: "#0d47a1"
}

committed -> free: "GC\nMinTSN past MaxTSN" {
  style.stroke: "#757575"
  style.stroke-dash: 5
}

# ── Crash Recovery Path ──────────────────────────────────────

pending -> void: "CRASH\n(recovery on startup)" {
  style.stroke: "#c62828"
  style.bold: true
}

void -> free: "GC\nMinTSN past MaxTSN" {
  style.stroke: "#757575"
  style.stroke-dash: 5
}

# ── Notes ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

note: |md
  **Critical invariant:** "UoW Created" WAL record must
  be durable before any revision uses this UoW ID.

  **Free = 0:** Zeroed memory is automatically Free.

  **WAL is authority:** Registry pages are a checkpoint
  cache. UoW state transitions are WAL records.

  **Two bitmaps (in-memory, rebuilt on startup):**
  - *Allocation*: tracks Free slots for O(1) alloc
  - *Committed*: crash-recovery fallback for visibility
| {
  shape: text
  style.font-size: 13
}
